{
  "text": "Our results also showed that at comparable Ramsay scores, BIS values were lower with dexmedetomidine sedation than with propofol. The results are similar to those of Recart et al. [CITATION_1] . Dexmedetomidine sedation differs from that of propofolinduced sedation [CITATION_2] . Patients who receive dexmedetomidine are quite comfortable and are still arousable and responsive to Table 4 . Time to spontaneous breathing, extubation and PACU stay in patients receiving dexmedetomidine or propofol. Values are mean (SD). *A P-value less than 0.05 was considered statistically significant.",
